					<description><![CDATA[<p>See what it takes to get a Google Knowledge Panel for your business, why it's important, and how you can earn yours now. </p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-knowledge-panel">How to Get a Google Knowledge Panel for Your Business (+Tips to Optimize It!)</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Getting a Google Knowledge Panel is like earning your business a big blue shiny checkmark in the search results‚Äîan official stamp of credibility that instantly builds trust. But it‚Äôs not like a listing that you can just set up and publish.</p>
<p>Your Knowledge Panel gets created by Google as a result of other activities across the web, and it can be a little tricky. So in this article, I‚Äôm going to share exactly what it takes to get a Google Knowledge Panel for your business.</p>
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#google-knowledge-panel-what-is-it">What is a Google Knowledge Panel?</a></li>
<li><a href="#google-knowledge-panel-benefits">Benefits of a Google Knowledge Panel</a></li>
<li><a href="#google-knowledge-panel-vs-google-business-profile">The difference between a Google Knowledge Panel and a Google Business Profile</a></li>
<li><a href="#google-knowledge-panel-how-to-get">How to get a Google Knowledge Panel</a></li>
<li><a href="#google-knowledge-panel-examples">Google Knowledge Panel examples</a></li>
<li><a href="#google-knowledge-panel-faqs">Google Knowledge Panel FAQs</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="google-knowledge-panel-what-is-it"></div>
<h2>What is a Google Knowledge Panel?</h2>
<p>A Google Knowledge Panel is the collection of information that appears on the upper right-hand side of your search results page (on desktop) when you search for a business, person, place, brand, or organization.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-knowledge-panel-example-png.avif" alt="google ads knowledge panel example" width="693" height="484" class="aligncenter wp-image-91098 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-knowledge-panel-example-png.avif 693w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-knowledge-panel-example-300x210.avif 300w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-knowledge-panel-example-480x335.avif 480w" sizes="(max-width: 693px) 100vw, 693px" /></p>
<p>The Knowledge Panel is part of Google‚Äôs Knowledge Graph, which uses existing, trusted data sources to surface quick, factual answers in the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/seo-trends-2025" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SERP</a>.</p>
<p><strong><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Ready to secure a Google Knowledge Panel for your business?</strong> Start with our<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/how-to-get-more-reviews?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_howtogetreviews_Download&amp;itm_source=localiq&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent_links" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> free guide on how to get more reviews</a>, complete with tips to boost ranking, reputation, and revenue!</p>
<div id="google-knowledge-panel-benefits"></div>
<h3>Benefits of a Google Knowledge Panel</h3>
<p>A Google Knowledge Panel gives your brand an official and<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/02/06/online-reputation-management" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> credible presence</a> in search results, <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-make-your-business-stand-out/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">helping you to stand out</a>, take up more real estate on the page, and surface key information at a glance. For businesses looking to build trust and visibility, it‚Äôs a powerful asset. Here are some quick benefits:</p>
<ul>
<li>Enhances trust and authority</li>
<li>Controls<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/11/02/brand-keywords" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> branded search</a> results</li>
<li>Boosts SEO and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/05/17/increase-online-presence" target="_blank" rel="noopener">online presence</a></li>
<li>Improves discoverability across platforms</li>
</ul>
<div id="google-knowledge-panel-vs-google-business-profile"></div>
<h2>Google Knowledge Panel vs. Google Business Profile: What‚Äôs the difference?</h2>
<p>Your Google Knowledge Panel is not the same as your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-business-profile-features">Google Business Profile</a> (GBP), which is your listing that also appears on the right-hand side of the SERP. Here‚Äôs a chart that helps to illustrate their differences, thanks to ChatGPT:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-knowledge-panel-benefits-png.avif" alt="google knowledge panel - google business profile comparison" width="785" height="431" class="aligncenter wp-image-91099 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-knowledge-panel-benefits-png.avif 785w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-knowledge-panel-benefits-300x165.avif 300w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-knowledge-panel-benefits-768x422.avif 768w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-knowledge-panel-benefits-480x264.avif 480w" sizes="(max-width: 785px) 100vw, 785px" /></p>
<p>While Google may use information from your GBP in its Knowledge Graph, having a GBP doesn‚Äôt guarantee you‚Äôll have a Knowledge Panel. A Knowledge Panel requires:</p>
<ul>
<li>Strong online presence</li>
<li>Structured data</li>
<li>External authority sources (like Wikidata, news, etc.)</li>
</ul>
<p>Let‚Äôs dive into that.</p>
<div id="google-knowledge-panel-how-to-get"></div>
<h2>How to get a Google Knowledge Panel for your business</h2>
<p>If you‚Äôre trying to get a Google Knowledge Panel for your business, you‚Äôve got your work cut out for you in five key areas:</p>
<h3>1. Request a Knowledge Panel claim</h3>
<p>For starters, search your business name and see if a panel already exists. If it does, click the three dots next to your company category and choose ‚ÄúClaim this knowledge panel.‚Äù</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-knowledge-panel-examples-png.avif" alt="google knowledge panel - example knowledge panel on serp" width="496" height="504" class="aligncenter wp-image-91095 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-knowledge-panel-examples-png.avif 496w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-knowledge-panel-examples-295x300.avif 295w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-knowledge-panel-examples-480x488.avif 480w" sizes="(max-width: 496px) 100vw, 496px" /></p>
<p>From there, follow the steps to get verified.</p>
<p><strong><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6a8.png" alt="üö®" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> This<a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLTheDefinitiveGuideBrandAwareness.html?cid=Web_WS_InContent_BrandAwareness_Guide_Download" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> definitive guide to brand awareness</a> can help you build your online presence for an optimized Google Knowledge Panel!</strong></p>
<h3>2. Claim and optimize your Google Business Profile</h3>
<p>As we mentioned above, your Google Business Profile doesn‚Äôt guarantee a Knowledge Panel, but it does influence it. Here‚Äôs what you can do:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-claim-a-business-on-google/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Claim your Google Business Profile</strong></a><strong>. </strong>This will allow you to edit your business information, respond to reviews, and more. Use our post for more detailed tips and instructions.</li>
<li><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/optimize-google-my-business-listing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Optimize your Google Business Profile</strong></a><strong>. </strong>Provided you‚Äôve claimed your profile, you can optimize it with reviews, photos, and regular updates.</li>
</ul>
<h3>3. Build your online presence</h3>
<p>There are a few <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/03/05/seo-strategy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">buckets of SEO</a> to focus on to help secure your Google Knowledge Panel:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Your listings.</strong> This is essentially your local SEO, which means making sure your business name, contact information, and descriptions are consistent across listings. Our <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/local-seo-checklist/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">local SEO checklist</a> can help with this.</li>
<li><strong>Keyword-targeted content. </strong>Use our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/04/06/on-page-seo" target="_blank" rel="noopener">on-page SEO</a> guide to make sure you‚Äôre writing quality, authoritative content that ranks.</li>
<li><strong>About us page.</strong> A strong About us page that includes your founding date, founders and leadership, location, products and services, industry, and other key milestones can help legitimize your business as well as other profiles across the web.</li>
<li><strong>Schema markup. </strong>This is a type of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/09/15/what-is-schema-markup" target="_blank" rel="noopener">structured data</a> that you add to your website‚Äôs HTML to help search engines understand the meaning behind content as opposed to just the words on the page. Schema types that will help the most here are Organization, LocalBusiness, Person, SameAs, Logo, URL, ContactPoint, and Address.</li>
</ul>
<p>Here‚Äôs an example of schema markup for my company (Hatch):</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-knowledge-panel-example-schema-png.avif" alt="google knowledge panel - example schema code" width="583" height="469" class="aligncenter wp-image-91097 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-knowledge-panel-example-schema-png.avif 583w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-knowledge-panel-example-schema-300x241.avif 300w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-knowledge-panel-example-schema-480x386.avif 480w" sizes="(max-width: 583px) 100vw, 583px" /></p>
<p>You can use a tool like <a href="http://schema.org">schema.org</a> to generate schema markup.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f50d.png" alt="üîç" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Find the right keywords to target in your SEO strategy with our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/keywords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_Keywords_KWTool" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Free Keyword Tool</a>!</strong></p>
<h3>4. Build your online authority</h3>
<p>In addition to building up your own content, you‚Äôll also want to get featured in other trusted content. This is where networking and <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/digital-marketing/influencer-marketing-tips/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">influencer marketing</a> come into play. Here are some ways to get featured in content across the web:</p>
<ul>
<li>Press releases</li>
<li>Interviews</li>
<li>Podcasts</li>
<li>Backlinks</li>
</ul>
<p>Use our <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/influencer-outreach/">influencer outreach email templates</a> or these <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/12/10/link-building-secrets">backlinking strategies</a> to get started.</p>
<h3>5. Get listed on key sites</h3>
<p>This tactic is similar to the one we just talked about, since it‚Äôs about getting mentions on websites other than your own, but this time we‚Äôre referring to specific sites that have heavy influence on Knowledge Panel information. We‚Äôre also referring to official listings or profiles, as opposed to a featured article or mention in a blog post. Sites to get listed on include:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Wikidata:Main_Page"><strong>Wikidata</strong></a><strong>.</strong> Google pulls information directly from here. It‚Äôs like a giant fact sheet, all written in Google‚Äôs love language (structured data)</li>
<li><a href="https://www.wikipedia.org/"><strong>Wikipedia</strong></a><strong>.</strong> Google also loves Wikipedia. This is like the human-friendly version of Wikidata, which helps keep Google‚Äôs Knowledge Panel readable.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.crunchbase.com/"><strong>Crunchbase</strong></a><strong>.</strong> Google doesn‚Äôt pull from here as directly, but it‚Äôs still a trusted source. Think of it as your business resume ‚Äî third-party validation that helps build your credibility.</li>
<li><strong>Industry directories</strong> (for example,<a href="https://localiq.com/blog/angi-business-listing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Angi</a>, Houzz, and Thumbtack for home services or Avvo, Martindale-Hubbell, and Justia in the legal field.)</li>
</ul>
<p>A few notes: Just as we mentioned earlier when talking about SEO, it‚Äôs important to ensure that your information is consistent and accurate across each of these sites. Also, don‚Äôt try to game the system with these sites, especially the Wikis. They have strict guidelines in place precisely so these platforms can remain a trusted source of information.</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs a quick chart on Wikipedia vs Wikidata to help you understand their differences and how they impact your Knowledge Panel, thanks to ChatGPT.</p>
