		<title>How to Write Google Ads Like a Pro in 2025 (+Examples!)</title>
		<link>https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ads-copy</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Kristen McCormick]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 01 Apr 2025 14:58:11 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Google Ads]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.wordstream.com/?p=90565</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Write stand-out Google Ads with these tips, techniques, and tools. </p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ads-copy">How to Write Google Ads Like a Pro in 2025 (+Examples!)</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>This year, increased competition, AI-driven automation, privacy updates, and evolving consumer behaviors demand that your Google Ads ads be at the top of their game. And that can only come from writing ads that use precise, compelling, and data-driven ad copy.</p>
<p>In this article, we‚Äôre going to share everything you need to know to write Google Ads that maximize visibility, clicks, and conversions while optimizing your ad spend.</p>
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#google-ads-copy-technical-guidelines">Technical guidelines for writing Google Ads</a></li>
<li><a href="#google-ads-copy-best-practices">Google Ads copy best practices</a></li>
<li><a href="#how-to-write-google-ads-tips-and-tricks">Tips and tricks for writing the best Google Ads</a></li>
<li><a href="#google-ads-copy-examples">Google Ads copy examples</a></li>
<li><a href="#how-to-write-google-ads-tools">Tools to help your ad copywriting</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="google-ads-copy-technical-guidelines"></div>
<h2>Guidelines for writing Google Ads in 2025</h2>
<p>Google Ads offers a few different ad formats in 2025, so let‚Äôs first get acquainted with headlines, descriptions, character counts, and the like.</p>
<h3>Responsive Search Ads (RSAs)</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Headlines:</strong> Up to 15 headlines, 30 characters max</li>
<li><strong>Descriptions:</strong> Up to four descriptions, 90 characters max</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/how-to-write-google-ads-rsa-chart.webp" alt="how to write google ads - rsa example" width="651" height="401" class="aligncenter wp-image-90580 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/how-to-write-google-ads-rsa-chart.webp 651w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/how-to-write-google-ads-rsa-chart-480x296.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 651px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Responsive Search Ads can be tricky. Use our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/04/05/responsive-search-ad-copy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Responsive Search Ad template</a> for help managing the combinations without pulling your hair out.</p>
<h3>Responsive Display Ads</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Short headlines:</strong> Up to five, up to 30 characters each</li>
<li><strong>Long headline:</strong> One, up to 90 characters</li>
<li><strong>Descriptions:</strong> Up to five, up to 90 characters each</li>
<li><strong>Business name:</strong> Up to 25 characters</li>
<li><strong>Images:</strong> Up to 15 different images</li>
<li><strong>Logos:</strong> Up to five different logos</li>
</ul>
<h3>Performance Max Campaigns</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Headlines:</strong> Up to five, 30 characters max</li>
<li><strong>Long headlines:</strong> Up to 90 characters</li>
<li><strong>Description:</strong> One 60-character description (required)</li>
<li><strong>Long descriptions: </strong>1-4 descriptions, up to 90 characters each</li>
<li><strong>Business name:</strong> Up to 25 characters</li>
</ul>
<h3>Call Ads</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Headlines:</strong> Up to 2, each with a maximum of 30 characters.</li>
<li><strong>Descriptions:</strong> Up to 2, each allowing up to 90 characters.</li>
<li><strong>Business name:</strong> Up to 25 characters.</li>
<li><strong>Display path:</strong> Up to 15 characters.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> For more help planning out your Google Ads copy strategy,</strong> download our free, complete <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLAccountStructure.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_LastAccountStructureGuide_Download" target="_blank" rel="noopener">guide to the perfect Google Ads account structure</a>.</p>
<div id="google-ads-copy-best-practices"></div>
<h2>Best practices for writing Google Ads</h2>
<p>Here are some fundamental best practices for <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/04/21/adwords-ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">writing super-effective Google Ads</a>.</p>
<h3>Prioritize relevance</h3>
<p>The Google Ads algorithm is all about relevance. Make sure your ad copy is super relevant to your keywords and that your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/great-landing-pages">landing page</a> is super relevant to your ads. The more continuity there is, the better.</p>
<h3>Use keywords in headlines for better visibility</h3>
<p>This helps with relevancy, allowing you to match search intent, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/07/19/does-quality-score-still-matter">boost Quality Score</a> (which can lower CPC), and increase CTR. Two quick tips:</p>
<ul>
<li>See if you can use long-tail keywords for high-intent searches. For example, ‚Äúbest metal roof installers for storm protection.‚Äù</li>
<li>For shorter keywords, place them at the beginning of the headline to ensure visibility.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Use ad assets</h3>
<p>Use various<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/07/25/google-ads-extensions-guide"> ad assets</a> (formerly called &#8220;extensions‚Äù) to provide additional information and links, enhancing ad relevance and performance.</p>
<p>Popular ones include structured snippets, price, lead forms, sitelinks, location, and call assets.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-call-asset-example-ad-1-png.webp" alt="google ads copy - call asset " width="793" height="325" class="aligncenter wp-image-90583 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-call-asset-example-ad-1-png.webp 793w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-call-asset-example-ad-1-480x197.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 793px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Call asset example</em></p>
<h3>A/B test</h3>
<p>Even with responsive search ads doing the mixing and matching for you, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ab-testing-examples">you should still be testing different approaches with your ads</a>. You may even separate them into different campaigns based on an overall theme. After all, you only get so much visibility into the performance of each ad combination within a single RSA campaign.</p>
<p>Some things to test include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Short vs. long-tail keywords</li>
<li>Direct vs. benefit-driven phrasing</li>
<li>Urgency-focused vs. informational headlines</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/26a1.png" alt="‚ö°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Create ad copy that increases your Quality Score fast for a cheaper CPC</strong>¬†with our free guide to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/ways-to-save-money-in-google-ads?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_SaveMoneyinGoogleAds_Download" target="_blank" rel="noopener">saving money in Google Ads</a>!</p>
<div id="how-to-write-google-ads-tips-and-tricks"></div>
<h2>Tricks for writing high-performing Google Ads</h2>
<p>It‚Äôs one thing to follow best practices for Google Ads. It‚Äôs another to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/10/03/how-to-write-exceptional-ppc-ad-copy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">write exceptional Google ads</a>. Here are the techniques to employ, that go beyond best practices, to help you maximize conversions.</p>
<h3>Copywriting tricks</h3>
<p>Ah, copywriting. I‚Äôm in my natural habitat here. I could go on for days, but I‚Äôll keep it short:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Use emotion for high-performing headlines.</strong> We‚Äôve got over <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/01/13/best-words-and-phrases-for-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noopener">130 emotional words and phrases</a> for you to browse through, plus<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/06/21/emotional-ad-copy-examples" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> these examples of emotional ad copy</a> to inspire you.</li>
<li><strong>Use psychological techniques to boost CTR. </strong>There are several ways to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/09/01/psychology-copywriting-tips-examples" target="_blank" rel="noopener">use psychology in your ad copy</a>. You can appeal to moral values, scarcity, repetition, hyperbole, and more.</li>
<li><strong>Use social proof. </strong>Leverage testimonial quotes and stats to convey to your audience that others are happy with your product or service. This is the most powerful tool at your disposal.</li>
<li><strong>Use power words. </strong>Pair your keywords with <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/03/22/power-words" target="_blank" rel="noopener">power words</a>. Examples include &#8220;exclusive,&#8221; &#8220;proven,&#8221; &#8220;award-winning,&#8221; &#8220;instant,&#8221; &#8220;guaranteed,&#8221; and &#8220;effortless.&#8221;</li>
<li><strong>Offer the right balance.</strong> Use our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/04/05/responsive-search-ad-copy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">responsive ad copy template</a> to make sure you‚Äôre using the right mix of features, benefits, and pain points.</li>
<li><strong>Offer an incentive. </strong>The best way to stand out is to offer some sort of tangible incentive, like a discount, a free offer, or a high-demand feature.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-example-png.webp" alt="how to write google ads - google ad auto example" width="843" height="271" class="aligncenter wp-image-90577 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-example-png.webp 843w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-example-480x154.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 843px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Nothing like a little fear-based copy about overpaying to complete your Google ad copy.</em></p>
<p>For more resources on copywriting, check out these posts:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/08/24/google-ads-examples" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Eye-catching Google Ads examples (+takeaway tips)</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/01/03/ad-copy-examples" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The best ad copy examples</a></li>
</ul>
<h3>CTA tricks</h3>
<p>The more specific you are with your call to action, the better. Another pro tip: Tailor your CTA for the intent of your audience. For example:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Top of funnel:</strong> Learn More, See How It Works, Get the Guide, Explore Solutions</li>
<li><strong>Middle</strong>: Start Your Free Trial, Compare Plans, See Pricing, Schedule a Consult, Book a Demo</li>
<li><strong>Bottom:</strong> Talk to an Expert Now, Get Started Now, Sign Up &amp; Save 20%, Order Now &amp; Get Half Off,</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-example-ad-png.webp" alt="how to write google ads - dental google ads copy example" width="800" height="242" class="aligncenter wp-image-90576 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-example-ad-png.webp 800w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-example-ad-480x145.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 800px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>&#8220;Get dental implants in one day&#8221; is highly specific. Plus, this example has a nice nod to the importance of experience.</em></p>
<h3>Keyword tricks</h3>
<p>Try <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/04/17/dynamic-keyword-insertion-guide" target="_blank" rel="noopener">dynamic keyword insertion</a>. This feature will automatically insert the exact search term into the headline. For example: ‚Äú{KeyWord: Custom Window Installation} &#8211; Get a Free Quote.‚Äù</p>
<p>But you need to be careful with your template for this one because you can get some awkward phrasing. For example ‚ÄúNeed Fix Leaky Faucet Myself? Call Now!‚Äù or ‚ÄúGet Cheap Roofing Companies Near Me.‚Äù These will convey carelessness and disingenuousness (sidenote: wow, I thought for sure autocorrect was going to tell me this isn‚Äôt a word. I‚Äôm pumped).</p>
<h3>Targeting tricks</h3>
<p>With some Google Ads campaign types (Performance Max especially), you can upload customer lists, email lists, CRM data, past purchase behavior, and more for more <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ads-audience-targeting">precise targeting</a> and therefore more precise ad copy. What‚Äôs more, this is all <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/04/12/first-party-data">first-party data</a>, which is accurate, privacy-compliant, and insight-rich. Here are some examples:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Existing customers</strong> ‚Üí cross-sell to existing customers, promote a special offer to VIP customers, reengage dormant customers</li>
<li><strong>Existing leads</strong> ‚Üí win back old leads who visited your website or who booked a demo but never closed</li>
<li><strong>Website visitors</strong> ‚Üí retarget people based on pages they visited or cart behavior</li>
</ul>
<div id="google-ads-copy-examples"></div>
<h2>Well-written Google Ads copy examples</h2>
<p>Here are some <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/08/24/google-ads-examples">examples of Google Ads</a> that employ the best practices and techniques we‚Äôve covered:</p>
<p><strong>Ballin Law: </strong>CTA (get a free consultation), urgency (see how much your case may be worth in minutes), power words (award-winning), incentive (pay nothing until you win).</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-legal-png.webp" alt="how to write google ads - example legal google ads copy" width="721" height="340" class="aligncenter wp-image-90575 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-legal-png.webp 721w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-legal-480x226.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 721px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><strong>Marshall Building and Remodeling. </strong>Sitelink assets, power words (award-winning), CTA (get a quote), benefits (keep the wet and windy weather out), incentive ($0 down and free consultations).</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-quote-request-png.webp" alt="google ads copy - example of how to write a google ad" width="725" height="388" class="aligncenter wp-image-90574 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-quote-request-png.webp 725w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-quote-request-480x257.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 725px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><strong>Sarah Davis MD. </strong>Feature-heavy (affordable, same-day appointments, multilingual staff), sitelink asset.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-healthcare-png.webp" alt="google ads copy - how to write google ads dental example" width="923" height="251" class="aligncenter wp-image-90570 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-healthcare-png.webp 923w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-healthcare-480x131.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 923px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><strong>ServiceTitan.</strong> Benefit focus (get paid faster, grow your business, accelerate success, deliver amazing service), CTA (book a free demo), features (QB compatible, mobile app).</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/how-to-write-google-ads-example-png.webp" alt="google ads copy - example" width="604" height="460" class="aligncenter wp-image-90572 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/how-to-write-google-ads-example-png.webp 604w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/how-to-write-google-ads-example-480x366.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 604px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><strong>Intuit QuickBooks. </strong>Social proof (89% of customers agree), benefit (get a clear view of your finances).</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-example-intuit-png.webp" alt="google ads copy example - intuit quickbooks ad" width="957" height="319" class="aligncenter wp-image-90582 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-example-intuit-png.webp 957w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-example-intuit-480x160.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 957px, 100vw" /></p>
<div id="how-to-write-google-ads-tools"></div>
<h2>Tools to write Google Ads</h2>
<p>Let‚Äôs finish off with some tools to help you in your quest to write great Google Ads in 2025.</p>
<h3>Keyword tools</h3>
<p>With the<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/keywords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_Keywords_KWTool" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Free Keyword Tool</a> from WordStream, enter seed keywords or even a URL into the search bar, and you‚Äôll get a list of related terms, including monthly search volumes and competition levels. It‚Äôs pretty easy to spot those high-volume, low-competition keyword unicorns.</p>
<p>The <a href="https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/7337243?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads Keyword Planner</a> is also a free tool that helps you discover relevant keywords and analyze search volume, competition, and estimated CPC.</p>
<h3>Ad assessment tools</h3>
<p>With WordStream‚Äôs <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Free Google Ads Grader</a>, you‚Äôll get a free <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/google-ads-assessment/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">assessment</a> of the performance of your Google Ads against 10 key metrics, with actionable insights to help you improve your Quality Score, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ads-shared-budgets">reduce wasted spend</a>, and maintain impression share. You can catch more <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/01/10/free-google-ads-tools" target="_blank" rel="noopener">free Google Ads tools here</a>.</p>
<h3>Competitive research tools</h3>
<p>With tools like Semrush and Ahrefs, you can analyze your competitors&#8217; keywords, ad copy, and bidding strategies to help inform your strategy. They also offer keyword research capabilities, surfacing volume, competition, costs, and other trends.</p>
<h3>Copywriting tools</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-copywriting-tools" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AI copywriting tools</a> like ChatGPT and Copy.ai can be super helpful for coming up with ideas for ad copy, refining copy you‚Äôve already written, or reframing your copy for different techniques or emotions. Just remember to use these tools as a sidekick to your ad copywriting endeavors and not as a substitute for strategic thinking, brand voice consistency, and human creativity.</p>
<p>You can also try <a href="https://localiq.com/google-ads-ai-copy-tool/?cid=Web_LiQ_InContent_AICopyTool_AICT&amp;itm_source=localiq&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent_links" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LocaliQ&#8217;s Google Ads AI Copy Tool</a> to get headlines and descriptions to test in your Google Ads. Always review and tweak <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/google-ads-ai-copy-tool/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AI-generated Google Ads copy </a>to ensure it aligns with your campaign goals and resonates with your audience. You can start out using AI to write your Google Ads with these <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-prompts" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AI prompts</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-ai-prompt-png.webp" alt="google ads copy - how to use ai to write google ads copy" width="766" height="433" class="aligncenter wp-image-90571 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-ai-prompt-png.webp 766w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/google-ads-copy-ai-prompt-480x271.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 766px, 100vw" /></p>
<h2>Write great Google Ads in 2025</h2>
<p>Writing high-performing Google Ads in 2025 requires a mix of technical precision, strategic messaging, and creativity. By following the best practices and tips in this post and using the tools we recommended, you can craft ads that maximize visibility, clicks, and conversions while keeping costs in check.</p>
<p>Now it‚Äôs time to put these strategies into action! Remember, great ads don‚Äôt just get seen; they get results. For more help maximizing your Google Ads copy results, see how <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/marketing-services?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Demo_Blog_Demo" target="_blank" rel="noopener">our solutions</a> can streamline your ad copywriting and optimize your campaign performance in 2025 and beyond.</p>
