<div id="february-diversity-observances"></div>
<h2>February diversity, equity, and inclusion observances</h2>
<p>Alright, now it&#8217;s time to get into the marketing ideas. Let&#8217;s start with important dates and observances that can help you in your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/31/diversity-equity-inclusion-resources">diversity, equity, and inclusion efforts</a>.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Black History Month: </strong>Your Black History-related content should not actually be a marketing ploy but a genuine initiative to raise awareness and promote civil rights.<img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20black20history20month.png" alt="february marketing ideas black history month" width="800" height="544" class="aligncenter" /><br />
Here are some things you can do.</p>
<ul>
<li>Highlight prominent Black leaders in your industry‚Äîlawyers, politicians, scientists, artists, educators, and athletes who have shaped or are shaping American society or your industry.</li>
<li>Interview or feature <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/07/28/black-business-month">Black business owners</a>, influencers, or members of your community who are helping to make history.</li>
<li>Share quotes, little-known facts, and eye-opening stats about Black History‚Äîespecially those related to your industry or niche.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Tammy Baldwin&#8217;s birthday (Feb 11): </strong>Tammy Baldwin is the first openly LGBT woman elected to both houses of Congress. Post an inspiring quote from her on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/instagram-threads">Instagram Threads</a> or Facebook.</li>
<li><strong>Susan B. Anthony&#8217;s birthday (Feb 15):</strong> This famous female is a leader of the women‚Äôs suffrage movement who advocated for abolition, labor rights, equal pay and more. On this day, share an eye-opening statistic or inspirational quote to raise awareness.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-susan-anthony.webp" alt="February marketing ideas - Instagram post featuring Susan B Anthony trivia." width="369" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-88279 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-susan-anthony.webp 369w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-susan-anthony-185x300.webp 185w" sizes="(max-width: 369px) 100vw, 369px" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div id="meaningful-february-marketing-ideas"></div>
<h2>Meaningful February marketing ideas</h2>
<p>In addition to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/11/16/inclusive-holiday-marketing-ideas">inclusivity</a>, there are plenty of other themes during February that can help you with meaningful marketing. Showing your support for causes you care about is a great way to connect with your audience and express your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/06/09/company-core-values">core values</a>. Here are some ideas and examples.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6d1.png" alt="üõë" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Looking to optimize your search ads this month too?</strong> Get started with our free<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Google Ads Grader</a>!</p>
<h3>Heart Health Awareness Month</h3>
<p>So February isn‚Äôt all about that $1 pink balloon heart but also that invaluable organ inside of you that makes you tick. If your business is focused on health and wellness, this is a great marketing opportunity for you.</p>
<ul>
<li>Fitness centers and gyms can partner with a local health center for heart disease awareness or screenings (here are more <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/offline-marketing-ideas/">offline marketing ideas</a>).</li>
<li>Host special classes focusing on cardiovascular activity.</li>
<li>Write informative blog posts about heart health and risk factors. Use this time to market your business by educating your customers on leading healthy lives.</li>
<li>Give out a free heart-healthy gift with purchases or registrations.</li>
</ul>
<p>In the example below, this fitness center is giving out free heart rate monitors to those who join in the month of February.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20national20heart20month.png" alt="february marketing ideas national heart month" width="800" height="584" /></div>
<p>If you‚Äôre not a health or fitness business, no problem.</p>
<ul>
<li>Any business can sponsor a Healing Heart 5k, or donate a portion of their profits to a heart health-related nonprofit.</li>
<li>Think outside the box‚Äîpet hearts, artichoke hearts, hearts of remain, website health (the heart of a business marketing strategy, for example).</li>
</ul>
<p>P.S. Check out our list of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/02/04/valentines-day-messages-clients">Genuine Valentine&#8217;s Day Messages and Email Templates to Send to Customers</a></p>
<h3>Children‚Äôs Dental Health Month</h3>
<p>Dentists can certainly have a field day with this one, but other businesses can use this opportunity to teach parents and students about the importance of dental health.</p>
<ul>
<li>Daycares, fitness centers, and churches can host special classes about the importance of dental hygiene.</li>
<li>If you‚Äôre a dentist, you may offer to teach such classes. Or spruce up your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/08/29/dentist-websites">dentist website</a> with some extra decorations or promotions.</li>
<li>Ecommerce businesses can promote their oral hygiene products.</li>
<li>If you‚Äôre not a dentist, a simple social media post to bring your target audience‚Äôs attention to the cause can go a long way.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-kids-dental-month.webp" alt="February marketing ideas - Instagram post featuring children's dental advice." width="449" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-88277 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-kids-dental-month.webp 449w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-kids-dental-month-225x300.webp 225w" sizes="(max-width: 449px) 100vw, 449px" /></p>
<ul></ul>
<h3>Cancer Awareness Month</h3>
<p>In addition to having World Cancer Day, the whole month of February is dedicated to cancer awareness. Show your support on Facebook with a purple-themed post or initiative. You can encourage your <a href="/blog/ws/2016/10/19/get-more-instagram-followers">followers</a> to ‚Äúpurple‚Äù their profile, <a href="/blog/ws/2020/07/29/how-to-promote-a-product">promote your purple products</a>, or run a purple-themed contest.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20purple20your20profile.png" alt="february marketing ideas purple your profile" width="800" height="515" /></div>
<h3>Wear Red Day</h3>
<p>National Wear Red Day is focused on raising awareness for heart disease. On this day, you could:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/blog/ws/2019/05/21/facebook-ads-for-events">Host an event</a> in support of cardiovascular health and promote it on Instagram.</li>
<li>Promote your red products or give your social media profiles or homepage a red theme for the day.</li>
<li>Post an applicable picture to Instagram with an eye-opening stat. This is a great way to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/09/27/how-to-increase-instagram-engagement">increase Instagram engagement</a>.</li>
</ul>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20wear20red20day201.png" alt="february marketing ideas wear red day 1" width="747" height="354" /></div>
<h3>World Cancer Day</h3>
<p>You may also want to use some of your marketing muscle to promote awareness for World Cancer Day itself. This is a good option for health and fitness businesses. But any brand with a following can make a difference here, too.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-cancer-day.webp" alt="February marketing ideas - Instagram post about defeating cancer." width="427" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-88278 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-cancer-day.webp 427w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-cancer-day-214x300.webp 214w" sizes="(max-width: 427px) 100vw, 427px" /></div>
<div></div>
<div id="fun-february-marketing-ideas"></div>
<h2>Fun February marketing ideas</h2>
<p>Some of these are well-known, others not so much. Take a look and see which ones align with your brand voice and values.</p>
<h3>Presidents&#8217; Day</h3>
<p>Federal holidays like these are always versatile. Any industry can run a Presidents&#8217; Day sale‚Äîfor the day, the weekend, or the whole dang month. Here are some ideas:</p>
<ul>
<li>Run a presidential trivia night at your restaurant or even on social media.</li>
<li>Run a Presidents&#8217; Day <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/05/11/instagram-giveaways">giveaway on Instagram</a> or Facebook.</li>
<li>Create a Facebook event for your sale.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/february-marketing-ideas-presidents-day-facebook-event.png" alt="february marketing ideas - presidents day facebook event" width="600" height="605" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-56520" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/february-marketing-ideas-presidents-day-facebook-event.png 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/february-marketing-ideas-presidents-day-facebook-event-480x484.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>&gt;&gt; Get more <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/february-blog-ideas">February blog, video, and other content ideas</a> here.</p>
<h3>Ice Cream for Breakfast Day</h3>
<p>Ironically, in the middle of Children‚Äôs Dental Health Month is Ice Cream for Breakfast Day&#8230;oops? But who says you can‚Äôt use this quirky holiday to <a href="/blog/ws/2014/06/12/marketing-ideas">market your business</a>?</p>
<p>Held on the first Saturday of February, this is an opportunity for bakeries, ice cream shops, or restaurants to run <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/10/13/sales-promotion-examples">special promotions</a>.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20ice20cream20for20breakfast20day-e1705690545574.png" alt="february marketing ideas ice cream for breakfast day" width="800" height="600" class="alignnone wp-image-10131 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20ice20cream20for20breakfast20day-e1705690545574-800x551.png 800w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20ice20cream20for20breakfast20day-e1705690545574-480x270.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 800px) 800px, 100vw" /></div>
<div>If you&#8217;re not in the confectionery industry, here are some other ideas:</div>
<ul>
<li>Let your <a href="https://localiq.com/local-marketing-lab/local-social-media-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">local social media</a> followers know where they can celebrate the day.</li>
<li>Host a virtual ice cream for a breakfast party.</li>
<li>Ask your followers to share their ice cream sundaes.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Galentine&#8217;s Day</h3>
<p>We&#8217;re not focused on <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/valentines-day-marketing/">Valentine&#8217;s Day marketing</a>¬†here, but that doesn&#8217;t mean we&#8217;re not going to have some fun with one of the best events in February: Galentine&#8217;s Day.</p>
<p>Galentine&#8217;s Day was first discussed on the sitcom Parks and Rec. In the show, Leslie Knope explains that &#8220;February 13th, Galentine&#8217;s Day, is about celebrating lady friends.&#8221; The cast of characters enjoy the day with gifts and brunch. But you can get as creative as you like. Here are a few ideas:</p>
<ul>
<li>Create a Galentine&#8217;s gift guide filled with fun little gifts friends can bring to hand out at the celebration.</li>
<li>Partner with a few brands and giveaway a Galentine&#8217;s gift box (and get lots of cross-promotion).</li>
<li>Offer a Galentine&#8217;s discount, and promote it across all of your channels.</li>
<li>Publish a guide to celebrating Galentine&#8217;s Day with party ideas, fun activities, and more.</li>
<li>For physical locations, hold a Galentine&#8217;s Day get-together with decorations, beverages, and one-day-only deals and services.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-galentines.webp" alt="February marketing ideas - Instagram post promoting Galentine's Day products." width="403" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-88285 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-galentines.webp 403w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-galentines-202x300.webp 202w" sizes="(max-width: 403px) 100vw, 403px" /></p>
<p><span><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4e3.png" alt="üì£" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Put these February marketing ideas to work with our free guide:¬†</span><a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite30BestWaysToPromote.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_Marketing_The30BestWaysToPromoteYourBusiness_Download" class="waffle-rich-text-link">The 30 Best Ways to Promote Your Business (With or Without Money)</a></p>
<h3>Love Your Pet Day</h3>
<p>Love Your Pet Day is February‚Äôs opportunity for you to shamelessly post about your pet. But here are some additional ideas to consider:</p>
<ul>
<li>Write a blog post about what your pet can teach you about [topic relevant to your industry].</li>
<li>Have your employees share photos of their pets and put the montage on social media or in your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-marketing-trends-2025?utm_source=facebook&amp;utm_medium=organic_social&amp;utm_campaign=blog?utm_source=Threads&amp;utm_medium=organic_social&amp;utm_campaign=blog&amp;utm_term=post" target="_blank" rel="noopener">February newslette</a>r.</li>
<li>Come up with a pet-themed incentive. For example, Select Hotels invited its followers to comment on its post with their favorite moments with their pets, and that if they did, ‚ÄúA surprise awaits the two of you on your next visit.‚Äù</li>
</ul>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20love20your20pet20day20giveaway.png" alt="february marketing ideas love your pet day giveaway" width="647" height="414" /></div>
<h3>Make a Friend Day</h3>
<p>This day gives you lots of opportunities for creative marketing.</p>
<ul>
<li>Send out a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/07/16/how-to-ask-for-reviews">review request</a> email themed around asking your customers to be your friend. (Use these <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/february-email-subject-lines/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">February email subjet lines</a> for inspiration!)</li>
<li>Partner with a neighboring or complementary business and run a joint friends promotion.</li>
<li>Remind people of your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/04/14/referral-program-ideas">referral program</a> or run a one-day special where referrals result in a discount or gift.</li>
</ul>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20refer20a20friend.png" alt="february marketing ideas refer a friend" width="600" height="474" /></div>
<h3>Groundhog Day Contest</h3>
<p>This superstitious day happens on February 2 every year. For the uninitiated, if the groundhog sees its shadow, winter will last six more weeks. If it does not see its shadow, spring will arrive early. Plenty of fun marketing material to work with here.</p>
<ul>
<li>Run a sale where the offer is contingent upon the outcome of the day.</li>
<li>Create content inspired by the Groundhog Day movie, sharing tips to break up the monotony or avoid repeating mistakes.</li>
<li>On Groundhog Day, you can run a contest, share a question or poll with your audience, or simply share a fun fact about the day.</li>
</ul>
<div><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20groundhog20day.png" alt="february marketing ideas groundhog day" width="463" height="473" class="aligncenter" /></div>
<h3>Super Bowl</h3>
<p>The Super Bowl is one of the most watched programs on television. How does your target audience relate to football? Are they football fans? Spouses or parents of football fans? Athletes? Is your business located near a Superbowl venue? Run a special during Superbowl weekend, create Superbowl-themed products, or share a helpful tip relevant to what their Superbowl experience will be like.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-super-bowl-2.webp" alt="February marketing ideas - Instagram Reel featuring Super Bowl products." width="425" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-88283 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-super-bowl-2.webp 425w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-super-bowl-2-213x300.webp 213w" sizes="(max-width: 425px) 100vw, 425px" /></p>
<div style="text-align: center;"></div>
<div><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Get even more marketing ideas to use year-round with our complete list</strong> of over <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteBestOnlineMarketingTips.html?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_130marketingtips_Download" target="_blank" rel="noopener">130 top marketing tips for more traffic, leads, and sales</a>!</div>
<p><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/february-social-media-holidays-and-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"></a></p>
<div id="february-hashtag-marketing-ideas"></div>
<h2>February hashtag marketing ideas</h2>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/05/29/instagram-hashtags">Hashtags</a> can expand your reach and add some personality to your posts. Here are some basic February hashtags to play around with.</p>
<h3>#Febsale</h3>
<p>If you‚Äôre just getting started with your Instagram marketing, start basic with something as simple as a #Febsale. In the below example, the small business Mexicali took a snapshot of their ready-to-ship orders to promote their February sale and encourage people to buy.</p>
<p>They didn‚Äôt use a photo shoot or fancy Photoshop graphics; just a simple behind-the-scenes sneak peek and a caption that closes with a question.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20febsale.png" alt="february marketing ideas febsale" width="733" height="468" /></div>
<h3>#FebruaryFeels for mood</h3>
<p>You don‚Äôt need to have a sale for a February-friendly Instagram post. How about just appealing to your audience‚Äôs mood during this time of year?</p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20febuary20feels.png" alt="february marketing ideas febuary feels" width="745" height="476" /></div>
<p>Just make sure you‚Äôre appealing to the mood of your specific audience in February as it relates to your business. Is your audience&#8230;</p>
<ul>
<li>Filing tax forms?</li>
<li>Returning back to school after break?</li>
<li>Reading love stories and seeking positive vibes?</li>
<li>Totally embracing singledom?</li>
</ul>
<p><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/monthly-email-newsletter-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"></a></p>
<h3>#FebruaryFeels for a testimonial</h3>
<p>Look back through your photos or even <a href="/blog/ws/2014/04/28/user-generated-content">user-generated content</a>. Can you repurpose any of them for a #FebruaryFeels-inspired <a href="/blog/ws/2015/05/05/customer-testimonials">testimonial</a>, as the Australian Girls Choir does below?</p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20febuary20feels20testimonial.png" alt="february marketing ideas febuary feels testimonial" width="745" height="355" /></div>
<h3>#FebruaryFavorites to promote other content</h3>
<p>This is a good way to surface seasonal content or products or even to bring to light some of the forgotten ones. Share a roundup of your most popular products or services, or even your favorite tips, <a href="/blog/ws/2018/07/06/digital-marketing-tools">tools</a>, products, or resources related to your audience‚Äôs goals and needs.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20febuary20favorites20content_0.png" alt="february marketing ideas february favorites content" width="800" height="373" /></div>
<h3>#FebruaryFeature to promote products</h3>
<p>Whether the <a href="/blog/ws/2020/07/29/how-to-promote-a-product">product you&#8217;re promoting</a> is February-themed or not, you can make it so by <a href="/blog/ws/2015/07/02/twitter-hashtags">using the hashtag</a> #Februaryfeature. Pick something you‚Äôd like to promote in February and see if #Februaryfeature can help<a href="/blog/ws/2018/04/02/retail-marketing"> increase sales</a> and engagement related to it.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20february20feature.png" alt="february marketing ideas february feature" width="800" height="419" /></div>
<h3>#FebruaryFeature to feature an employee</h3>
<p>You could also feature an employee, student, or customer. These types of feature posts can get your employees, customers, and fans excited about your business. Plus, they‚Äôll want to share their ‚Äúcelebrity‚Äù post with their network, which can help increase your reach.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20february20feature20employee.png" alt="february marketing ideas february feature employee" width="600" height="424" /></div>
<h3>#Februarychallenge</h3>
<p>Many people are coming down off their New Year&#8217;s resolutions (or maybe they purposefully avoided making them). That makes this hashtag a great option for February. Use it to encourage your audience to take on a new task or reach a goal they&#8217;ve been eyeing. Or, just have a little fun with it!</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-february-challenge.webp" alt="February marketing ideas - Instagram post using february challenge hashtag." width="348" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-88276 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-february-challenge.webp 348w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/february-marketing-ideas-february-challenge-174x300.webp 174w" sizes="(max-width: 348px) 100vw, 348px" /></p>
<h3>#FreshStartFebruary</h3>
<p>Another theme you can take advantage of in your February Instagram marketing is #FreshStartFebruary. This is especially applicable for businesses in the health and wellness industry.</p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/february20marketing20ideas20fresh20start20february1.png" alt="february marketing ideas fresh start february1" width="600" height="325" /></div>
<div></div>
<p>As you can see, there is much more to February than Valentine&#8217;s Day (but we have plenty of <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/valentines-day-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Valentine&#8217;s Day marketing ideas here</a>). Use the ideas (and these <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/winter-puns">winter puns</a>) above for creative and quality engagement with your audience‚Äîthe best way to market your business. And don‚Äôt forget about March! If you have events or promotions planned for Saint Patrick‚Äôs Day or other holidays, get your audience in the know.</p>
<p>For more monthly marketing ideas, here&#8217;s our full list:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/blog/ws/2020/12/07/january-marketing-ideas">January</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/01/11/february-marketing-ideas">February</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/02/09/march-marketing-ideas">March</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/03/08/april-marketing-ideas">April</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/04/05/may-marketing-ideas">May</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/05/10/june-marketing-ideas">June</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/06/07/july-marketing-ideas">July</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/07/08/august-marketing-ideas">August</a></li>
